description:
&lt;p&gt;Poplars Unit, In-patient Mental Health unit for Older People, Mayer Way, Houghton Regis, Beds LU5 5BF&lt;br /&gt;Band 3 Occupational Therapy Assistant&lt;br /&gt;Full Time - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen on Poplars, an acute inpatient Assessment Unit for Older People with mental illness within the Luton Directorate, Older Peoples Mental Health service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for someone with an understanding of mental health and working with older people and Occupational Therapy. The post holder will be responsible for providing specialist Occupational Therapy intervention under the guidance of the Occupational Therapist.&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will work within the already well-established multi-disciplinary team to promote and facilitate the OT programme both on the ward and in the community through 1:1 intervention, group work, and enabling clients in accessing relevant local community resources which would support their discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are regular Ward meetings and Trust wide Occupational Therapy meetings, opportunities for personal development, supervision and yearly appraisal and support from the unit manager and the Head Occupational Therapist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you have these skills and wish to work with a supportive team who strive to achieve high standards please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further information or a visit please contact Debbie Alaluf Head Occupational Therapist on 07836675697&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name :Debbie Alaluf&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head OT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: debbie.alaluf@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01234 310589&lt;/p&gt;
